## Why This Is Asked
This question tests the ability to design a cross-stream, windowed join with per-key ordering under backpressure—a common pattern in production systems like Databricks Structured Streaming and MongoDB Change Stream implementations.

## Key Concepts
- **Cross-stream joins with per-device keys**: Joining sensor readings (stream A) with status updates (stream B) requires partitioning by device ID to co-locate related events.
- **5-second tumbling windows and watermarks**: Tumbling windows provide non-overlapping, fixed-size time boundaries; watermarks track event time progress and enable safe window completion.
- **Per-key buffers and ordered emission**: Each device maintains separate queues per stream, ensuring in-order processing within each device partition.
- **Backpressure and dynamic worker scaling**: Backpressure signals prevent memory exhaustion when downstream processing cannot keep pace; workers adapt to throughput changes.
- **Late-data handling policy**: Events arriving after the watermark but within the allowed lateness threshold are replayed from buffers to maintain correctness.

## Code Example
```javascript
class WindowManager {
  constructor(windowSec) {
    this.windowSize = windowSec * 1000;
    this.buffers = new Map();
    this.watermark = 0;
    this.pendingJoins = new Map();
  }

  onEvent(event, stream) {
    const key = event.deviceId;
    const timestamp = event.timestamp;

    if (!this.buffers.has(key)) {
      this.buffers.set(key, { A: [], B: [] });
    }

    const buffer = this.buffers.get(key);
    buffer[stream].push(event);
    buffer[stream].sort((a, b) => a.timestamp - b.timestamp);

    this.watermark = Math.max(this.watermark, timestamp);
  }

  processWindow() {
    const windowEnd = this.watermark - (this.watermark % this.windowSize);
    const windowStart = windowEnd - this.windowSize;

    for (const [key, buffer] of this.buffers) {
      const joined = this.joinBuffers(buffer, windowStart, windowEnd);
      if (joined.length > 0) {
        this.emit(joined, key);
      }
    }
  }

  joinBuffers(buffer, start, end) {
    const results = [];
    const relevantA = buffer.A.filter(e => e.timestamp >= start && e.timestamp < end);
    const relevantB = buffer.B.filter(e => e.timestamp >= start && e.timestamp < end);

    for (const a of relevantA) {
      for (const b of relevantB) {
        if (Math.abs(a.timestamp - b.timestamp) <= 1000) {
          results.push({ ...a, ...b });
        }
      }
    }
    return results;
  }

  emit(joined, key) {
    console.log(`Emitting ${joined.length} joined events for device ${key}`);
  }
}

// Usage
const wm = new WindowManager(5);
wm.onEvent({ deviceId: 'dev1', timestamp: 1000, type: 'A', value: 23 }, 'A');
wm.onEvent({ deviceId: 'dev1', timestamp: 1500, type: 'B', status: 'active' }, 'B');
wm.processWindow();
```

