## Code Example
```javascript
class TelemetryPipeline {
  constructor(deviceIds, windowSize, queueCapacity, numWorkers) {
    this.deviceQueues = new Map();
    this.deviceState = new Map();
    this.globalQueue = new BoundedQueue(queueCapacity);
    this.workers = [];

    for (const id of deviceIds) {
      this.deviceQueues.set(id, []);
      this.deviceState.set(id, { seq: 0, window: [] });
    }
    this.resize(numWorkers);
  }

  publish(deviceId, ts, metric, seq) {
    if (this.globalQueue.isFull()) {
      return { accepted: false, backpressure: true };
    }
    this.globalQueue.push({ deviceId, ts, metric, seq });
    return { accepted: true };
  }

  dispatch() {
    const record = this.globalQueue.pop();
    if (!record) return;
    const state = this.deviceState.get(record.deviceId);
    if (record.seq < state.seq) {
      return; // late data: discard or log
    }
    state.window.push({ ts: record.ts, metric: record.metric });
    while (state.window.length > this.windowSize) state.window.shift();
    state.seq = record.seq;
  }

  rollingAverage(deviceId) {
    const win = this.deviceState.get(deviceId)?.window || [];
    return win.reduce((s, r) => s + r.metric, 0) / win.length;
  }

  resize(newSize) {
    while (this.workers.length < newSize) {
      this.workers.push(setInterval(() => this.dispatch(), 0));
    }
    while (this.workers.length > newSize) {
      clearInterval(this.workers.pop());
    }
  }
}
```

## Test Plan
1. **Functional correctness**: Verify per-device ordering with concurrent publishers injecting records with known sequence numbers; assert late/out-of-order records are handled per policy.
2. **Backpressure**: Fill the global queue and confirm `publish()` returns backpressure signal; verify publishers pause/resume correctly.
3. **Sliding window**: Inject N records per device and assert rolling average matches `sum(last W) / W`; test boundary cases (W=1, W=∞).
4. **Dynamic resizing**: Start with M workers, resize to M±N mid-operation, assert no records lost or duplicated.
5. **Clock skew**: Inject records with timestamps in the past; verify late data policy (discard/warn) is applied consistently.
6. **Stress test**: Run N publishers × high frequency against M workers, monitor memory and throughput under sustained load.

