## Why This Question Is Asked

This problem tests the ability to manage per-user ordering guarantees across a mutable worker pool under backpressure, while handling late-arriving data. It is representative of real-world analytics pipelines where events arrive out of order and must be re-sequenced efficiently without sacrificing throughput.

## Key Concepts

- **Per-user in-order delivery**: Ensuring events for each user are processed sequentially regardless of worker assignment.
- **Per-key replay buffers**: Temporary storage for out-of-order events with gap tracking to detect missing sequences.
- **Backpressure signaling**: Preventing producer overload by throttling or rejecting events when the system is saturated.
- **Late-event policy**: Defining how to handle events that arrive after their expected window (e.g., drop, delay, or flag).
- **Work-stealing vs. fixed partitions**: Trade-offs between load balancing efficiency and state locality.

## Code Example

```javascript
class UserStreamBuffer {
  constructor(maxGaps = 100) {
    this.nextSeq = 0;
    this.buffer = new Map();
    this.maxGaps = maxGaps;
  }

  add(event) {
    if (event.seq === this.nextSeq) {
      this.nextSeq++;
      return [event, ...this.flushBuffer()];
    }
    if (event.seq > this.nextSeq) {
      if (this.buffer.size >= this.maxGaps) {
        return { dropped: event, reason: 'gap_overflow' };
      }
      this.buffer.set(event.seq, event);
      return [];
    }
    return { dropped: event, reason: 'stale_event' };
  }

  flushBuffer() {
    const ready = [];
    while (this.buffer.has(this.nextSeq)) {
      ready.push(this.buffer.get(this.nextSeq));
      this.buffer.delete(this.nextSeq++);
    }
    return ready;
  }
}

class DynamicWorkerPool {
  constructor(size, processFn) {
    this.size = size;
    this.processFn = processFn;
    this.workers = Array.from({ length: size }, (_, i) => this.spawnWorker(i));
    this.queue = [];
  }

  spawnWorker(id) {
    return { id, busy: false };
  }

  async submit(event) {
    const worker = this.workers.find(w => !w.busy);
    if (!worker) {
      return { rejected: true, backpressure: true };
    }
    worker.busy = true;
    this.processFn(event).finally(() => { worker.busy = false; });
  }

  resize(newSize) {
    if (newSize > this.size) {
      for (let i = this.size; i < newSize; i++) {
        this.workers.push(this.spawnWorker(i));
      }
    } else if (newSize < this.size) {
      this.workers.splice(newSize).forEach(w => w.terminate?.());
    }
    this.size = newSize;
  }
}
```

